37
00:05:25.053 --> 00:05:38.053
do pretty good. But… that's not enough. We know that. So that's why there is this second model which is called the hybrid model or the accelerated computing model, where.


38
00:05:38.053 --> 00:05:42.053
You work in a combination of CPUs and GPUs.


39
00:05:42.053 --> 00:05:49.053
Intel CPUs have confidential computing. NVIDIA GPUs have confidential computing.


40
00:05:49.053 --> 00:06:06.053
So you can get them together. And you can have a good end-to-end story of confidential computing going from CPUs into GPUs. So, essentially, it is one extended trusted execution environment between CPUs and GPUs.


41
00:06:06.053 --> 00:06:19.053
Okay? There are two models for doing it. In the near term, you know, it's called a software-based model. You know, for folks who are familiar, they call it the bounce buffer solution where.


42
00:06:19.053 --> 00:06:23.053
The CPU writes into a buffer. It's an encrypted form.


43
00:06:23.053 --> 00:06:29.053
The GPU picks it up from the buffer and the CPU and the GPU share the secret.


44
00:06:29.053 --> 00:06:38.053
So things are encrypted, put on the buffer, GPUs pick up from there in the encrypted form. They have the secret, so decrypt it and they run it in the GPS.


45
00:06:38.053 --> 00:06:42.053
But in the longer term, year and a half, two years out.


46
00:06:42.053 --> 00:06:46.053
you don't need this software solution, it's all done in hardware.


47
00:06:46.053 --> 00:07:04.053
The PCIe bus gets encrypted. And then there is a negotiation between the CPUs and the GPUs on how they trust each other and there are proofs for trust, and then they pass that information in a very, very efficient way between the CPUs and the GPUs.


