00:10:18.053 --> 00:10:21.053
Or the GPUs, in case you're running it in GPUs.


72
00:10:21.053 --> 00:10:36.053
Okay, so that's the benefit of confidential computing, okay? Remember I talked to you about attestation, okay? Without attestation, confidential computing doesn't mean anything, okay? Your cloud provider told you, hey, I'm giving you an instance of confidential compute.


73
00:10:36.053 --> 00:10:39.053
But do you know for sure you got it?


74
00:10:39.053 --> 00:10:46.053
That's where attestation comes in. Attestation is going to give you a cryptographic proof that.


75
00:10:46.053 --> 00:10:50.053
You are, in fact, running in a confidential computing environment.


76
00:10:50.053 --> 00:10:57.053
that is genuine to the provider of it. It could be Intel, it could be AMD, it could be NVIDIA GPUs.


77
00:10:57.053 --> 00:11:02.053
You have proof that you are running in a legitimate, confidential computing environment.


78
00:11:02.053 --> 00:11:08.053
It is patched correctly. to the level that you are satisfied with?


79
00:11:08.053 --> 00:11:15.053
And then more importantly, your workloads that are running in are exactly what you expected them to be.


80
00:11:15.053 --> 00:11:22.053
If you are running a container, you would have a measurement of it, and you can verify that measurement to be what it needs to be.


81
00:11:22.053 --> 00:11:28.053
That's what attestation provides you. Okay? There are multiple ways of doing attestation again.


82
00:11:28.053 --> 00:11:35.053
You can, uh… I'm going to come back to that previous one.


