114
00:15:26.053 --> 00:15:38.053
Maybe a few, okay? So, very quickly… Google confidential space is like a data clean room for AI, okay? What it is, is you can take your containers.


115
00:15:38.053 --> 00:15:48.053
You run it in a confidential computing environment. The OS that runs inside that VM.


116
00:15:48.053 --> 00:15:54.053
your application, which is your container, everything is measured.


117
00:15:54.053 --> 00:16:04.053
And that measurements are available for verification. And the confidential space environment as part of launching your container.


118
00:16:04.053 --> 00:16:17.053
will attest to Intel Trust Authority. And the trust authority verifies all the policies that need to be verified, and it's going to give a token, which is called an attestation token.


119
00:16:17.053 --> 00:16:23.053
This token is now given to all the data sources.


120
00:16:23.053 --> 00:16:32.053
Whether it is a data source in Google Cloud, whether it's a data source in Amazon, or whether it's on-prem for you.


121
00:16:32.053 --> 00:16:39.053
that token is like your proof to the identity of identity.


122
00:16:39.053 --> 00:16:49.053
that your access control and management systems will verify, and based on that verification, they give access to the data to that workload.


123
00:16:49.053 --> 00:16:56.053
So, in the example that you see here, the AI workload is that green box that is there.


124
00:16:56.053 --> 00:17:04.053
The entire red box is the TDX environment. Everything inside that is measured, and it is verified.


125
00:17:04.053 --> 00:17:16.053
And that verification token is what is provided to the Google Cloud and the Amazon AWS protected resources. These are databases, keys, things like that.


126
00:17:16.053 --> 00:17:24.053
Only when those resources verify the token. They give the resource access token to that workload.


127
00:17:24.053 --> 00:17:37.053
And I'm sure folks who work on Google and AWS understand this very well. Without that resource access token, your workloads cannot access anything in those resources.


128
00:17:37.053 --> 00:17:44.053
