139
00:18:55.053 --> 00:19:01.053
So that they can fine-tune it, so that it's very… the efficacy of the model gets better.


140
00:19:01.053 --> 00:19:06.053
But the problem is. One hospital's data.


141
00:19:06.053 --> 00:19:25.053
is not enough. to improve the efficacy of the model, you need the data from multiple hospitals, and we all know how important PII is and you know all the HIPAA regulations and all of that. So you have a bunch of mutually untrusting parties.


142
00:19:25.053 --> 00:19:30.053
or distrusting parties. that need to cooperate with each other.


143
00:19:30.053 --> 00:19:39.053
To improve the efficacy of the model. The model owner is worried that if they put the model somewhere.


144
00:19:39.053 --> 00:19:49.053
their intellectual property is… could be lost. So they become another untrusted party as well, distrusted party in this case.


145
00:19:49.053 --> 00:19:58.053
So what do they do? They encrypt everything with the Tala Cipher trust key management system.


146
00:19:58.053 --> 00:20:09.053
So everybody, hospital A, B, C, before they bring the data, they provision a key in the Cypher Trust platform.


147
00:20:09.053 --> 00:20:15.053
they get their encryption key, and they encrypt the model, and encrypt the data sets.


148
00:20:15.053 --> 00:20:19.053
the model owner does exactly the same thing as well.


149
00:20:19.053 --> 00:20:27.053
They get the key from the CypherTrust platform, they encrypt their whatever that image diagnostic model is.


150
00:20:27.053 --> 00:20:35.053
And they bring all these encrypted collateral into a confidential computing environment.


151
00:20:35.053 --> 00:20:42.053
And once the CypherTrust platform talks to an attestation system like Intel Trust Authority.


152
00:20:42.053 --> 00:20:56.053
It verifies them, and based on the individual policies, it releases the decryption keys into that trusted execution environment. The middle box that you see with CPUs and GPUs.


153
00:20:56.053 --> 00:21:05.053
the datasets get decrypted there, the model gets decrypted there, the model gets fine-tuned there for whatever period of time.


154
00:21:05.053 --> 00:21:12.053
The datasets get deleted. The model gets re-encrypted. sent back to the model owner.


155
00:21:12.053 --> 00:21:19.053
Now, the model has been fully fine-tuned with multiple hospital data.


156
00:21:19.053 --> 00:21:27.053
And it is encrypted back to the model owner and they deliver it to the individual hospitals.


157
00:21:27.053 --> 00:21:34.053
So what did we get with this thing? The model owner's IP is protected. There is guarantee that nobody.


158
00:21:34.053 --> 00:21:38.053
saw what's in the model, nobody can steal the model.


159
00:21:38.053 --> 00:21:42.053
The datasets that are coming from the various hospitals.


160
00:21:42.053 --> 00:21:47.053
Nobody sees the data except the model training process.


161
00:21:47.053 --> 00:21:58.053
So their security requirements are met as well. And then the ultimate benefit is the efficacy of the model got better because it got trained on multiple hospital data sets.


